<sec id="summary">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <p><monospace>cartography</monospace> is an R package (R Core Team
  (<xref alt="2016" rid="ref-R" ref-type="bibr">2016</xref>)) for
  thematic mapping. It allows various cartographic representations such
  as proportional symbols, chroropleth, typology, flows or
  discontinuities. In addition it also proposes some useful features
  like cartographic palettes, layout (scale, north arrow, title…),
  labels, legends or access to cartographic API to ease the graphic
  presentation of maps.</p>
  <p>The package relies mostly on <monospace>sp</monospace> (Pebesma
  &amp; Bivand
  (<xref alt="2005" rid="ref-sp2005" ref-type="bibr">2005</xref>), R. S.
  Bivand et al.
  (<xref alt="2013" rid="ref-sp2013" ref-type="bibr">2013</xref>)) and
  <monospace>rgeos</monospace> (R. Bivand &amp; Rundel
  (<xref alt="2016" rid="ref-rgeos" ref-type="bibr">2016</xref>))
  packages to handle and transform spatial data.</p>
  <p>The map below is a cartographic composition showing most of the
  representations enabled by the package.</p>
